Two officials of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Onotu Joseph, 32, and Francis Igboh, 35, have been arraigned for the alleged murder of one Samuel Odion aged 38. The two officials were arrested last week after Odion’s body was exhumed from where it was buried. They were alleged to have beaten Odion to death on October 14 this year at Owa Hill, Benin-Asaba Road. The suspects were arraigned on a two-count charge of conspiracy and murder. The charge sheet reads in part, “That you Onotu Joseph ‘m’  and Francis Igboh ‘m’  had on or about the 14th of  October, 2019, at about 12.00hrs at Owa Hill, Benin-Asaba  Express Road, in the Benin Judicial Division did conspire amongst yourselves to commit felony to wit: Murder and thereby committed an offence punishable under Section 324 of the Criminal Code Cap 48, Vol. 11, laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria 1976 now applicable in Edo State.” Presiding judge, Justice Ohimai Ovbiagele remanded the two in prison custody  and fix hearing on November 12, 2019. Speaking to journalists, the State Counsel, Peter Ugwumba said the suspects were arraigned for justice to be served, adding that the case had been referred to the Edo State Legal Department for advice.